# Architecture — ChristMeets

## Layout

The feature-first migration is complete. Code lives under `lib/core/` (cross-cutting)
and `lib/features/<name>/` (feature slices). Only the app shell stays at the root.

```
lib/
  core/
    theme/         # app_typography, app_icons, app_illustrations
    constants/     # *_options (gender, faith, denomination, ...), relationship_intent
    utils/         # geo_utils, firestore_value_utils
    models/        # block_source, profile_photo_urls
    navigation/    # app_navigator (rootNavigatorKey)
    widgets/       # app_icon, app_dialog, app_back_button, profile_avatar,
                   #   profile_photo_placeholder, user_profile_bottom_sheet, ...
    photo/         # profile_photo_picker + crop screens + face_crop_helper
    onboarding/    # onboarding_requirements, onboarding_prompt_catalog (shared by
                   #   onboarding + profile)
  features/
    auth/ chat/ discovery/ matches/ onboarding/ profile/ settings/
      data/         # Repositories + legacy *Service classes (Firestore access)
      domain/       # OPTIONAL — pure, Firebase-free logic
      presentation/ # screens + widgets/
  main.dart            # entry point + auth UI
  main_navigation.dart # app shell / bottom-nav host
  widgets/nav_tab_badge.dart  # app-shell-only widget
```

- **All imports use `package:christian_dating_app/...`** — no relative `../` imports across
  folders. Keep this when adding files.
- `go_router` for auth gate, shell routes, and chat deep links — **implemented** in
  `core/navigation/app_router.dart` (`goRouterProvider`, `AppRoutes`). `rootNavigatorKey`
  and `matchPopupNavigatorObserver` remain for global overlays.
- **No feature imports another feature's internals.** If two features need the same code,
  it belongs in `core/` (that is why `onboarding_requirements` lives in `core/onboarding/`).
- When adding a new feature, create it under `lib/features/<name>/` with the same
  `data/ · domain/ · presentation/` shape.

## What goes in `core/`

Keep `core/` intentionally minimal. Put something there **only if both** are true:

1. It is used by **2+ features** (actually, not "might be someday").
2. **No single feature owns it** — it is genuinely cross-cutting.

If only one feature uses it, keep it inside that feature even if it feels generic.

- **Default to the feature.** Promote to `core/` only when a **second** feature actually
  needs it — do not pre-place things in `core/` "in case" they get shared.
- Already in `core/`: theme (`core/theme/app_typography.dart`), navigation
  (`core/navigation/app_navigator.dart` / `rootNavigatorKey`), shared UI primitives
  (`core/widgets/app_dialog.dart`, `app_back_button.dart`, `app_icon.dart`,
  `profile_avatar.dart`), shared constants
  (`core/constants/*_options.dart`), and the photo-crop module (`core/photo/`).
  Batch profile loads use `ProfileRepository.fetchProfilesByIds`.
- Stays in a feature: `match_unread.dart` / `liked_you_filters.dart` → `matches/domain/` (pure logic; unread writes in `ChatRepository`),
  `profile_completion.dart` / `height_utils.dart` → `profile/domain/`, `discovery_*` widgets →
  `discovery/presentation/widgets/`, `auth_repository.dart` → `auth/data/`,
  `issue_report_repository.dart` → `settings/data/`.

## Inside a feature folder

```
features/<name>/
  data/           # Firebase/API access (existing *Service classes)
  presentation/   # screens + widgets
  domain/         # OPTIONAL — pure, Firebase-free logic; add only when such logic exists
```

- Use 2 layers by default (`data` + `presentation`); add `domain/` only when a feature
  already has pure logic to hold (e.g. discovery filters, unread counts, completion %).
- **No `domain/` for CRUD-only features** (e.g. `auth/` is mostly Firebase side effects).
- `data/` never imports `presentation/`; `presentation/` never calls Firebase directly.
- `domain/` has **no Firebase imports** — keeps it unit-testable.
- Full Clean Architecture (entities + repository interfaces + use-cases) is **not** required;
  this is a single-source (Firebase) app.

## Enforced rules

1. **No Firebase in presentation.** Widgets and top-level UI helpers must not import
   `cloud_firestore`. Route reads/writes through a repository or core service.
2. **New features are feature-first** under `lib/features/<name>/`. Do **not** relocate
   legacy files as a side effect of an unrelated edit.
3. **One repository owns each domain's data access.** Reuse before adding queries.
   Feature repositories: `ProfileRepository`, `ChatRepository`, `MatchesRepository`,
   `DiscoveryRepository`. Device helpers live in feature `data/` layers
   (e.g. `LocationService` in `profile/data/`).
4. **Data layer returns app types, not Firestore types.** Never expose
   `DocumentSnapshot`, `QuerySnapshot`, or `Timestamp` to presentation/domain.
   Use `firestore_value_utils.dart` when parsing timestamp fields in pure logic.
   Onboarding deferred sign-up may use `FirebaseAuth` directly; profile I/O goes
   through `ProfileRepository`.

## Layer guidance (when adding or moving code)

**Core principle:** the data layer returns app types; presentation never imports `cloud_firestore`.

1. **UI** — screens and widgets; no direct Firestore in large widget trees when a service already exists.
2. **Services** — Firestore reads/writes, auth side effects, location/push helpers.
3. **Pure logic** — filters, unread counts, completion %; no Firebase imports.

Reuse existing services/repositories instead of duplicating queries:

- Profiles → `ProfileRepository` (`features/profile/data/`)
- Blocks → `BlockRepository` (`features/settings/data/`)
- Likes/matches list → `MatchesRepository` (`features/matches/data/`)
- Chat → `ChatRepository` (`features/chat/data/`)
- Discovery deck → `DiscoveryRepository` / `discoveryDeckProvider` (`features/discovery/presentation/discovery_deck_providers.dart`)
- Batch user profiles → `ProfileRepository.fetchProfilesByIds`
- Push → `PushNotificationService` + `pushNotificationServiceProvider` (`features/settings/data/`); FCM tokens → `ProfileRepository.addFcmToken` / `removeFcmToken`
- Issue reports → `IssueReportRepository` (`features/settings/data/`)
- Location / GPS → `LocationService` + `locationServiceProvider` (`features/profile/data/`)
- Profile photos → `ProfileImageRepository` (`features/profile/data/`)
- Auth → `AuthRepository` (`features/auth/data/`)

**Riverpod pattern (server-backed state):**

- `StreamProvider.autoDispose.family` for live Firestore streams keyed by uid/matchId
- `Provider` / `Provider.autoDispose.family` for derived counts and one-shot reads
- `ref.watch(provider)` in build; `ref.read(repoProvider)` in callbacks
- Top-level UI helpers without `ref`: `ProviderScope.containerOf(context).read(...)`

## File size

- Split files approaching ~1500+ lines when touching them for a large feature (e.g. `user_profile_discovery_card.dart`).
- Prefer feature-specific widgets over growing a single mega-widget.

## Cloud Functions

- Node functions in `functions/`; region `africa-south1` for Firestore triggers.
- FCM tokens stored on `users/{uid}.fcmTokens` (array).
